"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(*) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM account WHERE YEAR(STR_TO_DATE(date, '%Y-%m-%d')) = 1993)) AS percentage\nFROM \n    account\nJOIN \n    district ON account.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE \n    district.A2 = 'Decin' AND YEAR(STR_TO_DATE(account.date, '%Y-%m-%d')) = 1993;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of accounts from the 'Decin' district that were opened in 1993. It uses the `district` table to filter accounts by the district name and the `account` table to filter by the year of account creation."